==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maundy
<hw>Maun"dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Maundy
Thursday</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The sacrament of the Lord's
Supper.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The ceremony of washing the feet of the poor on
Maundy Thursday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The alms distributed in connection with this
ceremony or on Maundy Thursday.</def></p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In England, the foot washing is obsolete, but the
⟦ldquo⟧royal maundy⟦rdquo⟧ is distributed annually on behalf of the
sovereign. Since 1890 this distribution has been made from Westminster
Abbey.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maundy money</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Maundy coins</ent>⟦br⟧
